The paper deals with algorithmic problems on directed graphs, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on approximation algorithms and integrality gaps suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of asymmetric metrics and distances suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The study of linear programming relaxations suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
